By George eastern
(Education)
Education is not according. The latter is what
almost all students acquire in public elementary
and secondary schools. it consists of requiring
intervention that remains external to the pulse
of feeling, thinking, and experiencing that marks
the real life of the learned. To be schooled means
to be able to recipe names, dates, and events in
history but to be interactive to their significance
for one’c personal life and the contemporary
scene; or in be able to distinction among hedonistic. utilization, criticism Ethical theories but
'0 be interactive to the reasons for and certification of one! own behavior.
The process of according sends to be based
upon assumptions, generally explicit, regarding
the nature of the learned, the subject»matter, the
teacher, and the school. The learned is an creature person who needs to be “completed." His
proper place is to absorb what is extended to
him from without. Learning consists mainly at
passive. but hopefully efficient, absorption of
ready-made facts. At best the learned might be
an appreciate — an imitator of the master — at
worst a compliant spouse.
Subject matter is assumed to be respective of
an underlying reality structure independent or
time and place. Continuities in the development
of human life are arrested, discontinuities ignored
or unlimited. The present is largely a new expression of old trucks, The teacher is the price<
level repository of these unchanging trucks, His
training and status establish him as the chief
given of information and passed of judgment. l-air
task is to begin with a partially filled acceptable
and to end with having added to it appreciated.
The school is a systematic means of ensuring
cultural continuity and compliance with the familiar, tried, and tale. Its function is to incorporate: to fill-up the learned with the current values,
conceptual categories, facts, and attitudes.
The process of according produces a person in
us. culture who processes a body oi received
information at best tangential to the pulse of his
real life, who is driven by compromise competitiveness and magnetic acquisitiveness, and who is
shipped by an acute sense of dissonance between
the requirements of concerning to a tackedon
infrastructure of behavior and values and the de
hands of genuine experiencing. To be schooled
may, at best, mean that one is ready to be edt—
rated, at worst, that one has been handicapped.
The process of education is also based upon
generally explicit amumptlons. The learned is s
person in transit. as complete at any moment I:
he can be, c dynamic, acting agent who structures his world in the very process of processing
in Learning consists of I vital [rindic interaction
among learned, subject, and teacher. It is an active process of discovering and relating, particularly of relating received instructions to men
but-sense of reality. The learned is an active,
requiring agent, performer and specialty at once,
partner in the Continuous process of collecting
external and internal qualities.
Subject matter is relative to the perceived.
to time, place, to context. readings ate relative
to conceptualrlinguistic trademarks that may or
may not — 8 matter to be individually determined _ themselves be posted in "fundamenml,"
“universal,” “unchanging trucks." Knowledge is
continuously restrictions, progressively by each
generation, dramatically in response to plastic
change. The present is a particle of the novel,
the worn, the assure, the beautiful, the erroneous,
the arabic, and has sign' icanoe for the educated
person in direct proportion to the extent to which
be has made the present part of his genuine experiencing.
The teacher is in a colors, one of I region an
timely but alternatively seeking to know and to
experience the world. The teacher seeking to execute is first of all caught-up in the continuoutask being himself educated. He, too. is I person
in transit and, depending upon his river“, and the
conditions of the teaching setting, may be learn-
ing more than he is teaching. Teaching is a cooperative venture to which both learned and
teacher contribute in an attempt lo share internal qualities and to relate these to the "outer"
world with which they are in the process of interesting. The school is an instrument through
which the human being is both added in incorporating the conceptual categories, values, and
attitudes of his own and other cultures. and in
scrutinizing these originally in the light of his
developing sense of reality, truth, and cordless
The school is, therefore, no more a presented of
the past than a survivor of the fotos. it is an
instrument for establishing and purchasing I
process of critical, active experiencing, the outcome of which cannon, Ind ought not to be, predetermined.
The educated man knows himself, and through
this, knows covers; is dramatically sensitive to
those immediately around him, and, by enter—
sign, to all banking; whose knowledge is a genuine part oi his ongoing, real life; who has answered the basic techniques for requiring and
processing information in an era of information
explosion; and who, above all, realized he is A
person forever in the process of becoming.
What of Grinnell College? If one holds that
Grinnell freshmen have yet to be educated, may
be handicapped by their prior according, and that
being educated is a continuous task extending
throughout line’s life, the College has two main
tasks: remedies and preparation.
it is unlikely that “New Student Days" at any
limited period preceding freshman year is adequate to remedy the defects of according or even
to alert students to the difference between being
educated and schooled. The General Education
program might be viewed as a type of crash program that'could assist the student in making the
condition out of according to Education. But.do
the Historical Studies, Humanities, Foreign park
guide, Science, Fine Arts requirements do this?
Or do these courses largely give more of the
same — more according; or conduct the issue by
serving up both in an explained misalliallce? Do
the General Education courses stress education
as a preparation for a life-long process of critical
and passionate experiencing? is taking forty-plus
hours in one's major or focusing upon graduate
work and advanced degrees more conducted to a
according or to an education attitude? How is the
leather viewed at Grinnell — passive recipient,
Ipprenﬁoe, imitator of the learned master? is
it conducted to being educated to feel that one'l
task is basically to bishop on intellectual-Cultural
fare made available It s predetermined rate in
n master-Ipprcntfce context; or might not s relationship of shared, archive january into
matters that multi a personal difference to both
teacher and learned be more conducted In lchiev<
ing education for Ill concerned? Will one who
view- himself Is I passive receiver or previously
established trucks known best by u privileges
class be prepared to enter upon the life-long
process of becoming educated?
L! the altered nature of knowledge reflected
in department and division structures, in course
offerings, and in staffing policies of the College?
And how does Grinnell view itself as a school?
is it an instrument through which students and
faculty are added in the continuous process of
coming to know themselves and the world, or is
it mainly preoccupied with perpetuating a learned
class, learned provisions, operators of the masters? How often do the rewards go to the schooled
rather than to the educated? High grade point
average may represent awareness at according,
but is it an indication of having been educated?
Still, there are students who leave Grinnell
more educated than schooled; but is this the
rule, and, when achieved, the full of sellconscious planning? There are outcroppings of education at Grinnell that occur with it frequency
sufficient to recommend it as an institution generally striking to execute; but these outcroppingc
project horn a plain or according that friendly
needs wedding if such outcmppingii are not to in
covered like some lost temple.
 
