worked twelve to ﬁgreen hours a day
for two years conducting his investigation throughout Texas and the US. He
was invited by Chief Justice Warren [0
be a privileges observer of the Warren
Commission's inquiry and findings.
Altogether, he accompanied forty-five
volumes and portiollos of transcripts
tapes, shortcuts, documents and exhibits, before he began writing.
